- Tile images are cached in-memory so repeated nearby checks are instant
- Standard OSM tile server (tile.openstreetmap.org) supports CORS for canvas pixel reading"},"title":"Land detection with automatic snap-to-nearest-water using OSM tile pixel sampling"},"result":{"ok":true,"data":{"id":"cs_mqm4ggvv_c6ea3a4d-2952-4e9f-9425-dc3992aba9b1","sessionId":"session_mqlin5kw_29c2bdd2-6c8c-48f4-ae0c-6448b2869667","title":"Land detection with automatic snap-to-nearest-water using OSM tile pixel sampling","description":null,"status":"planning","plan":{"summary":"Add client-side land/water detection using OSM tile pixel sampling, and automatically snap the boat to the nearest water position when placed on land. The approach uses standard OpenStreetMap tiles (which have a consistent water color #aad3df) loaded into a hidden canvas. When the user drags the boat, clicks the map, or geolocates, we sample the pixel at that position on the OSM tile — if it's not water, we scan outward in expanding circles to find the nearest water pixel and snap the boat there with a toast notification.

