est water — {source} was on land'), sets corrected position; if no water found → shows toast ('No water nearby — position not changed'), keeps previous position. The `source` param is for the toast message ('drag', 'click', 'geolocation'). (req 1, 2, 3)","status":"pending"},{"id":"step_4","description":"Step 5 — Wire all position-setting events through the validator: Update the `dragend` handler, `map.on('click')` handler, geolocation success callback, and silent tryGeolocation callback to call `validateAndSetBoatPosition` instead of directly setting boatPosition/setLatLng/refreshData. Each passes its source label. (req 1, 2, 3)","status":"pending"},{"id":"step_5","description":"Step 6 — Add visual feedback CSS: Add a brief boat marker pulse/glow animation when the boat is snapped to water, so the user sees it was repositioned. Add to sailing-weather.css. (req 3)","status":"pending"},{"id":"step_6","description":"Step 7 — Tests and visual verification: Write tests validating the app still loads and the API works. Run check_export_types. Take screenshots to verify the feature. (all reqs)","status":"pending"}]},"planMessageIds":[1781945694207488],"approvalMessageId":1781945813220172,"workMessageIds":[1781946845230970,1781946853374301,1781946860745875,1781946893100798],"toolCalls":null,"reasoning":null,"tokenUsage":null,"createdAt":"2026-06-20T08:54:53.562Z","updatedAt":"2026-06-20T09:15:03.624Z","completedAt":null},"_changesetEvent":"changeset_updated","_changeset":{"id":"cs_mqm4ggvv_c6ea3a4d-2952-4e9f-9425-dc3992aba9b1","sessionId":"session_mqlin5kw_29c2bdd2-6c8c-48f4-ae0c-6448b2869667","title":"Land detection with automatic snap-to-nearest-water using OSM tile pixel sampling","description":null,"status":"in_progress","plan":{"summary":"Add client-side land/water detection using OSM tile pixel sampling, and automatically snap the boat to the nearest water position when placed on land. The approach uses standard OpenStreetMap tiles (which have a consistent water color